    <item>
      <title>JP Spinetto：现金不再在拉丁美洲占主导地位</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-06-26/el-efectivo-ya-no-reina-en-america-latina</link>
      <description><![CDATA[拉丁美洲的许多重大问题，从犯罪到不平等，似乎根深蒂固，无法解决。但有一个领域可以找到好消息：在非正规性和金融包容性这一关键问题上，该地区正在取得跨越式发展。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-06-26/el-efectivo-ya-no-reina-en-america-latina</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 26 Jun 2024 09:30:30 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>拉丁美洲现金不再为王</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-06-26/cash-is-no-longer-king-in-latin-america</link>
      <description><![CDATA[在以金融包容性较差而闻名的地区，数字和非现金支付正在蓬勃发展。政府和监管机构应推动这股浪潮，使金融服务的可及性更加公平。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-06-26/cash-is-no-longer-king-in-latin-america</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 26 Jun 2024 09:30:29 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
